<TITLE> B. League resumes Thursday with mid-term transfers closing Wednesday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 30 (bdnews24.con)  Four bottom teams of the B. League took part in the mid-term players' transfer till Wednesday evening, the final day of the bourse. The second leg of the first-ever professional football league starts Thursday with fourth-placed Muktijoddha Sangsad playing against the fifth-placed Chittagong Mohammedan Sporting Club at the Bangabandhu National Stadium. Dhaka Mohammedan Sporting Club topped the first-leg point-table with 20 points, one point behind the jointly second-placed Abahani Limited and Sheikh Russel KC, who have 19 points each. On the last day of the mid-term transfer, title contenders Abahani was waiting for Nigerian strikers Jeremiah and Ndem, who were scheduled to arrive in Dhaka Wednesday night from Kolkata. However, the sky-blues outfit were set to register Cameroon striker Ovi Michael John and Moroccan Khobashi Mohammad, who was released from Sheikh Russel KC. Abahani also maintained the registration of their foreign recruits, Awdu Ibrahim and Argentine defender Caparolo. Bottom-team Rahmatganj MFS with only two points got the highest seven players signed as they brought Nigerian Nche Francis and Arafat Ali Ronny from Dhaka Mohammedan on loan and also registered five new players -- Mohammad Mamun, Rasel Ansari, Nigerians Abayemi Felix and Adeyemo Olaleken. Tenth-ranked Chittagong Abahani with nine points followed Rahmatganj MFS with roping in six players. The port city sky-blues outfit took Anisur Rahman from Ctg MSC on loan and recruited five new players -- Monir Hossain, Surendra Kumar (Napal), Shantosh Shahukhal (Nepal) and Othello Banei (Liberia). The seventh-placed Arambagh KS with 13 points had three new players signed up.They are Mahmud Hasan Chowdhury, Biplob Kumar Bishnu, Tareq Hossain Khan. The eighth-placed Farashganj SC with 10 points registered two new players -- Kamote'Amodu (Guyana) and Opara Luxson Puma (Nigeria). 
